The registry key "Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Winlogon" contains several values related to system behavior and user interface settings. In this case, the "AutoRestartShell" value is set to 1, ensuring that the Explorer shell restarts automatically after a crash. Additionally, the "Shell" value is set to "Explorer.exe," indicating the default shell program.

There are no specific registry entries associated with the payload mentioned in the provided output. However, the "Userinit" value includes references to "userinit.exe" and "sdra64.exe," which could potentially be related to the payload or malicious activities. Further analysis of these executables and their behavior would be necessary to determine any malicious intent or activities.
